Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows impaired renal function (elevated creatinine), mild hypoglycemia, low total protein, metabolic acidosis (low CO₂), hyperchloremia, and dyslipidemia (high LDL, low HDL). These findings suggest possible chronic kidney disease with associated metabolic disturbances and increased cardiovascular risk. Clinical correlation and further evaluation are recommended.
